### Enable Custom Log Tags in Node.js Agent

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet demonstrates how to enable custom tags for logs in the New Relic Node.js agent. It shows configuration via both `config` object and environment variables. Enabling this feature allows for better log filtering and correlation.

```javascript
// Enable custom tags using config object
newrelic.configure({
  ...
  application_logging: {
    forwarding: {
      labels: {
        enabled: true
      }
    }
  }
  ...
});

// Enable custom tags using environment variable
// NEW_RELIC_APPLICATION_LOGGING_FORWARDING_LABELS_ENABLED=true
```

