### Exclude Labels from Logs in Node.js Agent

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet shows how to configure the New Relic Node.js agent to exclude specific labels from being added to logs. This is useful for preventing sensitive or redundant information from being included in log data. Configuration can be done via the `config` object or environment variables.

```javascript
// Exclude labels using config object
